title: Gold Prices Fall as Traders Book Profit After Rally
text: 0219 GMT [Dow Jones] Gold prices fell in Asian trade Monday as traders booked profits after a sharp rally end of last week as disappointing U.S. jobs report has led many investors to believe that a rise in interest rates may not occur soon. The jobs report showed the U.S. economy created 142,000 new jobs in September, far lower than expected.
